T1  - True Monopolistic Competition as a Result of Imperfect Information*
PY  - 1986
Y1  - 1986/08/01
DO  - 10.2307/1885694
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 101
IS  - 3
SP  - 493
EP  - 511
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - The paper restates Hart's [1985a, 1985b] definition of large group monopolistic competition, distinguishes it from oligopolistic competition, and raises the question of whether there are reasonable circumstances that give rise to true monopolistic competition as defined. The purpose is to show that consumers' imperfect information may create conditions that will turn an otherwise oligopolistic market into a truly monopolistically competitive one.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
