TY  - JOUR
AU  - Shapiro, Matthew D.
T1  - The Dynamic Demand for Capital and Labor*
PY  - 1986
Y1  - 1986/08/01
DO  - 10.2307/1885695
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 101
IS  - 3
SP  - 513
EP  - 542
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - A model of the dynamically interrelated demand for capital and labor is specified and estimated. The estimates are of the first-order conditions of the firm's problem rather than of the closed-form decision rules. This use of the first-order conditions allows a random rate of return and a flexible specification of the technology. The estimates do not imply the very slow rates of adjustment displayed in other, related estimates of the demand for capital. Because adjustment is estimated to be rapid, there is, contrary to the standard view, scope for factor prices to affect investment at relatively high frequencies.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1885695
ER  - 



