TY  - JOUR
AU  - Kamien, Morton I.
AU  - Tauman, Yair
T1  - Fees Versus Royalties and the Private Value of a Patent*
PY  - 1986
Y1  - 1986/08/01
DO  - 10.2307/1885693
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 101
IS  - 3
SP  - 471
EP  - 491
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We compare how much profit an owner of a patented cost-reducing invention can realize by licensing it to an oligopolistic industry producing a homogeneous product, by means of a fixed fee or a per unit royalty. Our analysis is conducted in terms of a noncooperative game involving n + 1 players: the inventor and the n firms. In this game the inventor acts as a Stackelberg leader, and it has a unique subgame perfect equilibrium in pure strategies. It is shown that licensing by means of a fixed fee is superior to licensing by means of a royalty for both the inventor and consumers. Only a “drastic” innovation is licensed to a single producer.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1885693
ER  - 



